<HEADLINE>
COMPANY NEWS 
</HEADLINE>
  
 (ATTN: GERMANY, Calif., N.J.)  (mk) 
 c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   _ Lucent Technologies Inc., Murray Hill, N.J., said it would
build a new semiconductor plant in Allentown, Pa., for $165
million, consolidating smaller facilities it has in the area.
</P>
<P>
   _ Imagyn Medical Technologies, Newport Beach, Calif., a
manufacturer and marketer of gynecological and urological medical
products, will sell its line of impotence products to Timm Research
Co. for $25.8 million.
</P>
<P>
   _ Prosieben Media A, Munich, Germany, will buy a 20 percent
stake in Arete Image Software as part of a wider alliance with the
U.S. special-effects software maker.
</P>
</TEXT>
