<TEXT>
<P>
   The Los Angeles Daily News plans to move the following general
stories for use by NYTimes News Service clients, AMs and PMs of
Sunday, Oct. 11 and thereafter. For questions about stories,
contact William Toren at the Daily News, (818) 713-3702.
</P>
<P>
   SANDWICH-GENERATION (Los Angeles) _ Ellen Sperling, 34, always
thought her father would live to cherish life as a grandparent. But
as Parkinson's disease and Alzheimer's-induced dementia began to
take their toll on her father their roles reversed _ She became the
parent and caretaker of an increasingly infantile, yet elderly man.
Sperling is among 2,000 people who have turned to the Los Angeles
Caregivers Association for help in coping with the stressful life
of a member of the ``sandwich generation'' _ Baby Boomers who are
raising their children while at the same time dealing with
dependent parents. Millions of Americans face similar generational
crunches. By Yvette Cabrera. (Will move in the ``a'' national and
``n'' California news file.)
</P>
<P>
   X X X
</P>
</TEXT>
