   (NYT12) NORTH HAVEN, Conn. -- Oct. 10, 1998 --
CONN-ANIMAL-TRAPPING, 10-10 -- Bill Mannetti, an animal rights
advocate for 12 years and founder of Animal Rights Front, has bid
on the exclusive right to trap animals on parcels of state property
-- then in effect declared the land a trap-free zone. ``We went to
the ground,'' says Mannetti. ``It's public land, our land. We had
no choice but to enter the program and, in a sense, to undermine
it. We'll spare some animals from very hard, cruel deaths.''
(George Ruhe/New York Times Photo)
