Children at the Tuxedo Park School on Oct. 10, 1940. Philip
Robinson, far left, Fiona Ross, far back right, and Maggie Ross,
fifth from left. The children were part of an effort, largely
arranged by a two-country organization, the Children's Overseas
Reception Board, under which about 5,000 British children were
evacuated to the United States early in World War II. (New York
Times Photo)
