<P>
   (NYT7) OSSINING, N.Y. -- Oct. 10, 1998 --
RUN-CHICAGO-MARATHON-1, 10-10 -- Khalid Khannouchi, 27, training
for Sunday's Chicago Marathon. He won Chicago last year in his very
first marathon, in 2 hours 7 minutes 10 seconds, then the
fourth-fastest time in history. Only four years earlier, Khannouchi
had come from Morocco to Brooklyn, washing dishes in a restaurant,
training after midnight on potholed streets, determined to make it
as a world-class runner. (George M. Gutierrez/New York Times Photo)
</P>
