 &HT;    Bills take on the Colts this afternoon
 &HT;    By Len Pasquarelli
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA _
</P>
<P>
   Bills at Colts, 1:01 p.m.
</P>
<P>
   -- Last week: Bills 26, 49ers 21; Colts 17, Chargers 12.
</P>
<P>
   -- Series: Bills lead 31-23-1.
</P>
<P>
   -- Notable: Last seven meetings have been decided by 6 points or
fewer, and total margin in last four games was 11 points. ...
Buffalo QB Rob Johnson has five TD passes to five receivers. ...
Despite turnovers, Indianapolis QB Peyton Manning leads AFC with
1,129 passing yards. ... Colts RB Marshall Faulk has rushed for a
touchdown in five of last six games against Buffalo. ... Bills DE
Bruce Smith has six sacks in last four games against the Colts.
</P>
<P>
   -- Favorite: Buffalo by 3.
</P>
<P>
   Panthers at Cowboys,1:01 p.m.
</P>
<P>
   -- Last week: Falcons 51, Panthers 23; Cowboys 31, Redskins 10.
</P>
<P>
   -- Series: Panthers lead 1-0.
</P>
<P>
   -- Notable: Emmitt Smith and Chris Warren went over 100 yards
last week, the first Cowboys RB tandem to do so since 1978. ...
Cowboys WR Michael Irvin needs seven catches for 700 in career and
No. 10 spot all-time. ... Panthers' 16 sacks are tied for
second-best in NFC; LB Kevin Greene leads league with nine. ...
Panthers allowed two highest point totals in club history in last
two games _ 37 to Green Bay and 51 to Atlanta. ... Since '93,
Cowboys are 17-4 in October, best in NFL.
</P>
<P>
   -- Favorite: Dallas by 7.
</P>
<P>
   Chiefs at Patriots, 1:01 p.m.
</P>
<P>
   -- Last week: Chiefs 17, Seahawks 6; Patriots 30, Saints 27.
</P>
