   SECOND-HALF ROUNDUP
</P>
<P>
   THIRD QUARTER: A scoreless third quarter was punctuated by
Tech's defensive play to stop a possible Wolfpack touchdown. Backup
QB Charles Berry had engineered a nice drive for State down to the
Tech 2 when he was sacked by Jesse Tarplin and fumbled, the ball
recovered by defensive lineman Tony Robinson. Perhaps the biggest
story of the quarter _ not to mention the game _ for the Jackets
defensively was their ability to keep the ball out of Holt's hands.
State's All-America WR candidate did not touch the ball in the
third quarter, and the only time he was an intended receiver, the
pass was knocked away beautifully by Bostic. Holt had just three
receptions, albeit for 93 yards, and returned two punts for 51
yards after 45 minutes in addition to the TD pass, but the Wolfpack
wasn't able to take advantage of his big-play abilities very often.
</P>
<P>
   FOURTH QUARTER: The teams traded TDs in a contest whose outcome
had been decided long before. Hamilton ran in from 5 yards out, and
the Wolfpack put together a 69-yard drive, capped by a 1-yard TD
catch by Coleman from Berry, who played well in relief of Barnette.
Hamilton finished Tech's fourth straight game with 40 points or
more on a 6-yard run with 3:11 to play. Berry responded with a
3-yard jaunt at the 2:14 mark.
</P>
