<SLUG> BC-FBC-TEXAS-A&AMP;M-DEFENSE-TEX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
CURRY'S SWIPE LAST OF BIG DEFENSIVE PLAYS
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By MIKE JONES 
c.1998 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   COLLEGE STATION, Texas _ What Nebraska was about to throw at the
Texas A&AMP;M defense on third-and-15 with 59 seconds to play, Aggies
cornerback Sedrick Curry didn't know.
</P>
<P>
   He and the rest of the A&AMP;M defense, which had dominated the
Cornhuskers most of the afternoon until two fourth-quarter scoring
drives, knew only two things.
</P>
<P>
   ``We didn't want to give up anything easy and we didn't want to
give up the deep ball,'' said Curry, who was in the game while
Jason Webster nursed a freshly sprained ankle.
</P>
<P>
   Nebraska quarterback Bobby Newcombe broke left out of the
shotgun to throw a pass, and Curry's subsequent interception broke
the Huskers' backs and preserved a monumental 28-21 upset.
</P>
<P>
   ``I saw Newcombe was scrambling and it seemed like their
receivers were cutting their routes short,'' Curry said. ``I
noticed his arm come up and I made a great break on the ball and
was able to get there before \Rtight end Sheldon Jackson\S did. It
was the biggest play of my career, no question.''
</P>
<P>
   To his credit, Curry kept his head, sliding to the turf with the
ball safely cradled in his arms at the Nebraska 48 after a 9-yard
return.
</P>
<P>
   ``My first thought was to take it to the house,'' Curry said.
``But then I said to myself, I believe I'd better get down and let
\Rthe offense\S run out the clock. Then it will be time to
celebrate.''
</P>
<P>
   Curry's interception put a lid on a day of big defensive plays
by the Wrecking Crew. Included was a series of three consecutive
sacks, the last resulting in outside linebacker Warrick Holdman's
end-zone recovery of a Newcombe fumble that was forced by nose
guard Ron Edwards. That put A&AMP;M up, 21-7, at 9:13 of the third
quarter.
</P>
<P>
   Then, after Nebraska took a 40-yard kickoff return and drove
toward the goal, the Aggies threw back the scoring threat. Webster
tackled Nebraska wide receiver Shevin Wiggins for a 4-yard loss on
fourth-and-two from the Aggies' 10. A&AMP;M then drove 86 yards for a
28-7 cushion.
</P>
<P>
   ``That was one of the big series in the game when they had the
good kick return against us and were coming right down the
defense's throat,'' A&AMP;M coach R.C. Slocum said. ``A big, big series
right there.
</P>
<P>
   ``There were a couple of long passes \Rlate\S that were really
irritating. We were in a situation at the end where we shouldn't
have let them get back into it. But overall, the defense was
spectacular.''
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
